{
  "texts": [
    "The name is motivated by a canonical affine connection on the fibres of M which encodes the local N-actions (see §2.1), and is key in the collapsing theory [CFG92].",
    "These solitons generalise in a natural way the well-known algebraic solitons from the homogeneous setting [LL13,Jab15,Jab14], and thanks to a forthcoming result [LP25], they indeed describe the general asymptotic behavior of immortal Ricci flows on closed manifolds that collapse with bounded cuvature and diameter.A second motivation comes from the recent non-existence results for invariant Einstein metrics of negative scalar curvature on (untwisted) principal bundles, see [BL23a,BL23b].",
    "As an upshot of the present paper, a plethora of examples can be constructed if one allows for the isometric actions to be defined only locally.Our first main result is the following dimension-reduction theorem, which makes no assumption on dim B: Theorem A.",
    "Let B be a closed manifold and N a simply-connected nilpotent Lie group.",
    "Any affine expanding Ricci soliton on a twisted principal bundle B × ρ N gives rise to a solution to the twisted harmonic-Einstein equations (4) for the pair (B, G/K), where G/K is a symmetric space of non-compact type naturally associated to N. Conversely, to each solution to (4) there corresponds an affine expanding Ricci soliton on B × ρ N.The twisted harmonic-Einstein equations for a pair (B, G/K) consisting of a smooth manifold B and a symmetric space of non-compact type G/K is the following coupled system of equations for a triple (g B, ρ, h), where g B is a Riemannian metric on B, ρ ∈ Hom(π 1 (B), G), and h: B → G/K is smooth and ρ-equivariant:(4) tr gB (∇dh) = 0, Ric(g B) = -1 2 gB + h * g sym."
  ]
}